Package org.jsapar.compose.bean

Classes for composing Java Beans as output.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BeanEventListener<T>
    Interface for receiving event call-backs while composing.
    BeanFactory<T>
    Interface for a bean factory that creates bean instances based on line content.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BeanComposeConfig
    Configuration that controls behavior while composing beans.
    BeanComposer<T>
    Composer class that composes java beans based on a document or by single lines.
    BeanEvent<T>
    Event that is generated each time a bean is composed by a BeanComposer
    BeanFactoryByMap<T>  
    BeanFactoryDefault<T>  
    RecordingBeanEventListener<T>
    Saves all beans that was composed into a list that can be retrieved by calling RecordingBeanEventListener.getBeans() when done composing.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BeanComposeException  

Package org.jsapar.compose.bean Description

Classes for composing Java Beans as output. The BeanComposer is the class that composes Document or Line into Java Beans.
